#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:22
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:24
msgid ""
"This document contains the release notes for the Clang C/C++/Objective-C "
"frontend, part of the LLVM Compiler Infrastructure, release |release|. Here "
"we describe the status of Clang in some detail, including major improvements "
"from the previous release and new feature work. For the general LLVM release "
"notes, see `the LLVM documentation <https://llvm.org/docs/ReleaseNotes."
"html>`_. For the libc++ release notes, see `this page <https://libcxx.llvm."
"org/ReleaseNotes.html>`_. All LLVM releases may be downloaded from the `LLVM "
"releases web site <https://llvm.org/releases/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:33
msgid ""
"For more information about Clang or LLVM, including information about the "
"latest release, please see the `Clang Web Site <https://clang.llvm.org>`_ or "
"the `LLVM Web Site <https://llvm.org>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:38
msgid "Potentially Breaking Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:41
msgid "C/C++ Language Potentially Breaking Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:44
msgid "C++ Specific Potentially Breaking Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:46
msgid ""
"Clang now more aggressively optimizes away stores to objects after they are "
"dead. This behavior can be disabled with ``-fno-lifetime-dse``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:50
msgid "ABI Changes in This Version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:52
msgid ""
"Fixed incorrect struct layout for ``_BitInt`` bitfields wider than 255 bits "
"on MSVC targets. Internal bitfield tracking fields were changed from "
"``unsigned char`` to ``uint64_t`` to prevent overflow. This might be an ABI "
"break for such structs compared to earlier Clang versions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:58
msgid "AST Dumping Potentially Breaking Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:60
msgid ""
"The JSON AST dump now includes all fields from ``AvailabilityAttr``: "
"``platform``, ``introduced``, ``deprecated``, ``obsoleted``, "
"``unavailable``, ``message``, ``strict``, ``replacement``, ``priority``, and "
"``environment``. Previously, these fields were missing from the JSON output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:66
msgid "Clang Frontend Potentially Breaking Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:68
msgid ""
"HIPSPV toolchain: `--offload-targets=spirv{32,64}` option is deprecated and "
"will be removed when the new offload driver becomes default. The replacement "
"for the option is `--offload-targets=spirv{32,64}-unknown-chipstar` when "
"using the new offload driver (`--offload-new-driver`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:73
msgid ""
"The new driver (`--offload-new-driver`) is now default for all offloading "
"compilations. This changes the ABI for relocatable device code. Currently, "
"libraries will need to be recompiled, or used with (`--no-offload-new-"
"driver`). This option will be removed in the next release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:81
msgid "Clang Python Bindings Potentially Breaking Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:82
msgid ""
"Remove ``CompletionString.Availability``. No libclang interfaces returned "
"instances of it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:83
msgid ""
"``CompletionString.availability`` now returns instances of "
"``CompletionString.AvailabilityKindCompat``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:85
msgid ""
"Instances of ``AvailabilityKindCompat`` have the same ``__str__`` "
"representation as the previous ``CompletionChunk.Kind`` and are equality-"
"comparable with the existing ``AvailabilityKind`` enum. It will be replaced "
"by ``AvailabilityKind`` in a future release. When this happens, the return "
"type of ``CompletionString.availability`` will change to "
"``AvailabilityKind``, so it is recommended to use ``AvailabilityKind`` to "
"compare with the return values of ``CompletionString.availability``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:91
msgid ""
"Remove ``availabilityKinds``. In this release, uses of ``availabilityKinds`` "
"need to be replaced by ``CompletionString.AvailabilityKind``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:93
msgid ""
"``CompletionChunk.kind`` now returns instances of ``CompletionChunkKind``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:95
msgid ""
"Instances of ``CompletionChunkKind`` have the same ``__str__`` "
"representation as the previous ``CompletionChunk.Kind`` for compatibility. "
"These representations will be changed in a future release to match other "
"enums."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:98
msgid ""
"Remove ``completionChunkKindMap``. In this release, uses of "
"``completionChunkKindMap`` need to be replaced by ``CompletionChunkKind``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:100
msgid ""
"Move ``SPELLING_CACHE`` into ``CompletionChunk`` and change it to use "
"``CompletionChunkKind`` instances as keys, instead of the enum values. An "
"alias is kept in the form of a ``SPELLING_CACHE`` variable, but it only "
"supports ``__getitem__`` and ``__contains__``. It will be removed in a "
"future release. Please migrate to using ``CompletionChunk.SPELLING_CACHE`` "
"instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:105
msgid ""
"``SourceLocation`` and ``SourceRange`` now use ``NotImplemented`` to "
"delegate equality checks (``__eq__``) to the other object they are compared "
"with when they are of different classes. They previously returned ``False`` "
"when compared with objects of other classes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:111
msgid "What's New in Clang |release|?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:114
msgid "C++ Language Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:116
msgid ""
"``__is_trivially_equality_comparable`` no longer returns false for all enum "
"types. (`#132672 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/132672>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:119
msgid "C++2c Feature Support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:122
msgid "C++23 Feature Support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:125
msgid "C++20 Feature Support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:127
msgid ""
"Clang now supports `P1857R3 <https://wg21.link/p1857r3>`_ Modules Dependency "
"Discovery. (`#54047 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/54047>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:130
msgid "C++17 Feature Support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:133
msgid "Resolutions to C++ Defect Reports"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:136
msgid "C Language Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:139
msgid "C2y Feature Support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:142
msgid "C23 Feature Support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:143
msgid ""
"Clang now allows C23 ``constexpr`` struct member access through the dot "
"operator in constant expressions. (`#178349 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-"
"project/issues/178349>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:146
msgid "Non-comprehensive list of changes in this release"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:148
msgid ""
"Added support for floating point and pointer values in most ``__atomic_`` "
"builtins."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:151
msgid ""
"Added ``__builtin_stdc_rotate_left`` and ``__builtin_stdc_rotate_right`` for "
"bit rotation of unsigned integers including ``_BitInt`` types. Rotation "
"counts are normalized modulo the bit-width and support negative values. "
"Usable in constant expressions. Implicit conversion is supported for class/"
"struct types with conversion operators."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:157
msgid ""
"A new generic bit-reverse builtin function ``__builtin_bitreverseg`` that "
"extends bit-reversal support to all standard integers type, including "
"``_BitInt``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:161
msgid ""
"Deprecated float types support from ``__builtin_elementwise_max`` and "
"``__builtin_elementwise_min``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:165
msgid "New Compiler Flags"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:166
msgid ""
"New option ``-fms-anonymous-structs`` / ``-fno-ms-anonymous-structs`` added "
"to enable or disable Microsoft's anonymous struct/union extension without "
"enabling other ``-fms-extensions`` features (`#177607 <https://github.com/"
"llvm/llvm-project/issues/177607>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:169
msgid ""
"New option ``--precompile-reduced-bmi`` allows build system to generate a "
"reduced BMI only for a C++20 importable module unit. Previously the users "
"can only generate the reduced BMI as a by-product, e.g, an object files or a "
"full BMI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:174
msgid ""
"New ``-cc1`` option ``-fexperimental-overflow-behavior-types`` added to "
"enable parsing of the experimental ``overflow_behavior`` type attribute and "
"type specifiers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:178
msgid ""
"New ``-cl`` option ``/d2guardnochecks`` added to match MSVC. When Windows "
"Control Flow Guard (CFG) is enabled by other options, it will instruct Clang "
"to emit the CFG metadata, but disable adding checks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:183
msgid "Deprecated Compiler Flags"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:186
msgid "Modified Compiler Flags"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:187
msgid ""
"The `-mno-outline` and `-moutline` compiler flags are now allowed on RISC-V "
"and X86, which both support the machine outliner."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:188
msgid ""
"The `-mno-outline` flag will now add the `nooutline` IR attribute, so that `-"
"mno-outline` and `-moutline` objects can be mixed correctly during LTO."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:192
msgid "Removed Compiler Flags"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:195
msgid "Attribute Changes in Clang"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:197
msgid ""
"Added new attribute ``stack_protector_ignore`` to opt specific local "
"variables out of the analysis which determines if a function should get a "
"stack protector.  A function will still generate a stack protector if other "
"local variables or command line flags require it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:202
msgid ""
"Added a new attribute, ``[[clang::no_outline]]`` to suppress outlining from "
"annotated functions. This uses the LLVM `nooutline` attribute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:205
msgid ""
"Introduced a new type attribute ``__attribute__((overflow_behavior))`` which "
"currently accepts either ``wrap`` or ``trap`` as an argument, enabling type-"
"level control over overflow behavior. There is also an accompanying type "
"specifier for each behavior kind via `__ob_wrap` and `__ob_trap`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:211
msgid "Improvements to Clang's diagnostics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:212
msgid ""
"Added ``-Wlifetime-safety`` to enable lifetime safety analysis, a CFG-based "
"intra-procedural analysis that detects use-after-free and related temporal "
"safety bugs. See the `RFC <https://discourse.llvm.org/t/rfc-intra-procedural-"
"lifetime-analysis-in-clang/86291>`_ for more details. By design, this "
"warning is enabled in ``-Weverything``. To disable the analysis, use ``-Wno-"
"lifetime-safety`` or ``-fno-lifetime-safety``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:219
msgid ""
"Added ``-Wlifetime-safety-suggestions`` to enable lifetime annotation "
"suggestions. This provides suggestions for function parameters that should "
"be marked ``[[clang::lifetimebound]]`` based on lifetime analysis. For "
"example, for the following function:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:228
msgid "Clang will suggest:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:240
msgid ""
"Added ``-Wlifetime-safety-noescape`` to detect misuse of ``[[clang::"
"noescape]]`` annotation where the parameter escapes through return. For "
"example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:247
msgid "Clang will warn:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:258
msgid ""
"Added ``-Wlifetime-safety-dangling-field`` to detect dangling field "
"references when stack memory escapes to class fields. This is part of ``-"
"Wlifetime-safety`` and detects cases where local variables or parameters are "
"stored in fields but outlive their scope. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:270
msgid ""
"Improved ``-Wassign-enum`` performance by caching enum enumerator values. "
"(`#176454 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/176454>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:272
msgid ""
"Fixed a false negative in ``-Warray-bounds`` where the warning was "
"suppressed when accessing a member function on a past-the-end array element. "
"(`#179128 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/179128>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:276
msgid ""
"Added a missing space to the FixIt for the ``implicit-int`` group of "
"diagnostics and made sure that only one such diagnostic and FixIt is emitted "
"per declaration group. (`#179354 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/"
"issues/179354>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:279
msgid ""
"The ``-Wloop-analysis`` warning has been extended to catch more cases of "
"variable modification inside lambda expressions (`#132038 <https://github."
"com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/132038>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:282
msgid ""
"Clang now emits ``-Wsizeof-pointer-memaccess`` when snprintf/vsnprintf use "
"the sizeof the destination buffer(dynamically allocated) in the len "
"parameter(`#162366 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/162366>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:285
msgid ""
"``-Wunsafe-buffer-usage`` now warns about unsafe two-parameter constructors "
"of ``std::string_view`` (pointer and size), consistent with the existing "
"warning for ``std::span``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:288
msgid ""
"Added ``-Wmodule-map-path-outside-directory`` (off by default) to warn on "
"header and umbrella directory paths that use ``..`` to refer outside the "
"module directory in module maps found via implicit search (``-fimplicit-"
"module-maps``). This does not affect module maps specified explicitly via ``-"
"fmodule-map-file=``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:295
msgid "Improvements to Clang's time-trace"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:298
msgid "Improvements to Coverage Mapping"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:300
msgid "[MC/DC] Nested expressions are handled as individual MC/DC expressions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:301
msgid ""
"\"Single byte coverage\" now supports branch coverage and can be used "
"together with ``-fcoverage-mcdc``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:305
msgid "Bug Fixes in This Version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:307
msgid ""
"Fixed atomic boolean compound assignment; the conversion back to atomic bool "
"would be miscompiled. (`#33210 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/"
"issues/33210>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:309
msgid ""
"Fixed a failed assertion in the preprocessor when ``__has_embed`` parameters "
"are missing parentheses. (`#175088 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/"
"issues/175088>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:310
msgid ""
"Fix lifetime extension of temporaries in for-range-initializers in "
"templates. (`#165182 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/165182>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:311
msgid ""
"Fixed a preprocessor crash in ``__has_cpp_attribute`` on incomplete scoped "
"attributes. (`#178098 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/178098>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:312
msgid ""
"Fixes an assertion failure when evaluating ``__underlying_type`` on enum "
"redeclarations. (`#177943 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/"
"issues/177943>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:313
msgid ""
"Fixed an assertion failure caused by nested macro expansion during header-"
"name lexing (``__has_embed(__has_include)``). (`#178635 <https://github.com/"
"llvm/llvm-project/issues/178635>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:314
msgid ""
"Clang now outputs relative paths of embeds for dependency output. (`#161950 "
"<https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/161950>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:315
msgid ""
"Fix the result type of a binary operation where both operands are 'void' l-"
"values. (`#111300 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/111300>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:316
msgid ""
"Fixed an assertion failure when evaluating ``_Countof`` on invalid ``void``-"
"typed operands. (`#180893 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/"
"issues/180893>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:317
msgid ""
"Fixed an assertion failure in the serialized diagnostic printer when it is "
"destroyed without calling ``finish()``. (`#140433 <https://github.com/llvm/"
"llvm-project/issues/140433>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:318
msgid ""
"Fixed an assertion failure caused by error recovery while extending a nested "
"name specifier with results from ordinary lookup. (`#181470 <https://github."
"com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/181470>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:319
msgid ""
"Fixed a crash when parsing ``#pragma clang attribute`` arguments for "
"attributes that forbid arguments. (`#182122 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-"
"project/issues/182122>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:320
msgid ""
"Fixed a bug with multiple-include optimization (MIOpt) state not being "
"preserved in some cases during lexing, which could suppress header-guard "
"mismatch diagnostics and interfere with include-guard optimization. "
"(`#180155 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/180155>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:323
msgid "Bug Fixes to Compiler Builtins"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:324
msgid ""
"Fixed a crash when calling `__builtin_allow_sanitize_check` with no "
"arguments. (`#183927 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/183927>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:327
msgid "Bug Fixes to Attribute Support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:328
msgid ""
"Fixed a behavioral discrepancy between deleted functions and private members "
"when checking the ``enable_if`` attribute. (`#175895 <https://github.com/"
"llvm/llvm-project/issues/175895>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:329
msgid ""
"Fixed ``init_priority`` attribute by delaying type checks until after the "
"type is deduced."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:332
msgid "Bug Fixes to C++ Support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:333
msgid ""
"Fixed a crash on error recovery when dealing with invalid templates. "
"(`#183075 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/183075>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:334
msgid ""
"Fixed a crash when instantiating ``requires`` expressions involving "
"substitution failures in C++ concepts. (`#176402 <https://github.com/llvm/"
"llvm-project/issues/176402>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:335
msgid ""
"Fixed an incorrect template argument deduction when matching packs of "
"template template parameters when one of its parameters is also a pack. "
"(`#181166 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/181166>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:337
msgid ""
"Fixed a crash when a default argument is passed to an explicit object "
"parameter. (`#176639 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/176639>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:338
msgid ""
"Fixed a crash when diagnosing an invalid static member function with an "
"explicit object parameter (`#177741 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/"
"issues/177741>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:339
msgid ""
"Fixed a crash when pack expansions are used as arguments for non-pack "
"parameters of built-in templates. (`#180307 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-"
"project/issues/180307>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:340
msgid ""
"Fixed a bug where captured variables in non-mutable lambdas were incorrectly "
"treated as mutable when used inside decltype in the return type. (`#180460 "
"<https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/180460>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:342
msgid ""
"Fixed a crash when evaluating uninitialized GCC vector/ext_vector_type "
"vectors in ``constexpr``. (`#180044 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/"
"issues/180044>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:343
msgid ""
"Fixed a crash on ``typeid`` of incomplete local types during template "
"instantiation. (`#63242 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/"
"issues/63242>`_), (`#176397 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/"
"issues/176397>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:344
msgid ""
"Inherited constructors in ``dllexport`` classes are now exported for ABI-"
"compatible cases, matching MSVC behavior. Constructors with variadic "
"arguments or callee-cleanup parameters are not yet supported and produce a "
"warning. (`#162640 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/162640>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:348
msgid ""
"Fix initialization of GRO when GRO-return type mismatches, as part of "
"CWG2563. (`#98744 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/98744>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:349
msgid ""
"Fix an error using an initializer list with array new for a type that is not "
"default-constructible. (`#81157 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/"
"issues/81157>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:352
msgid "Bug Fixes to AST Handling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:353
msgid ""
"Fixed a bug where explicit nullability property attributes were not stored "
"in AST nodes in Objective-C. (`#179703 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/"
"issues/179703>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:356
msgid "Miscellaneous Bug Fixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:357
msgid ""
"Fixed the arguments of the format attribute on ``__builtin_os_log_format``.  "
"Previously, they were off by 1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:360
msgid "Miscellaneous Clang Crashes Fixed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:362
msgid ""
"Fixed a crash when attempting to jump over initialization of a variable with "
"variably modified type. (`#175540 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/"
"issues/175540>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:363
msgid ""
"Fixed a crash when using loop hint with a value dependent argument inside a "
"generic lambda. (`#172289 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/"
"issues/172289>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:365
msgid ""
"Fixed a crash in C++ overload resolution with ``_Atomic``-qualified argument "
"types. (`#170433 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/170433>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:366
msgid ""
"Fixed a crash when casting a parenthesized unresolved template-id or array "
"section. (`#183505 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/183505>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:367
msgid ""
"Fixed a crash when initializing a ``constexpr`` pointer with a floating-"
"point literal in C23. (`#180313 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/"
"issues/180313>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:368
msgid ""
"Fixed an assertion when diagnosing address-space qualified ``new``/"
"``delete`` in language-defined address spaces such as OpenCL ``__local``. "
"(`#178319 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/178319>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:369
msgid ""
"Fixed an assertion failure in ObjC++ ARC when binding a rvalue reference to "
"reference with different lifetimes (`#178524 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-"
"project/issues/178524>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../ReleaseNotes.rst:370
msgid ""
"Fixed a crash when subscripting a vector type with large unsigned integer "
"values. (`#180563 <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/180563>`_)"
msgstr ""

